WWS_StoryItem:102250401.title: WITH LOVE
WWS_StoryItem:102250401.description:
By the grace of God, we are pleased to announce

our wedding to you, our family and friends.

WWS_StoryItem:100149613.title: Worth every mile between us
WWS_StoryItem:100149613.description: Dave and Eunike's lives intertwined when they met at Pensacola Christian College. What started as a friendship soon blossomed into a deep and meaningful connection. In 2018, they embarked on a romantic journey, discovering a love that would transcend time. Despite the challenges of a long-distance relationship that followed, Dave and Eunike persevered with unwavering commitment and a shared vision of their future together. The miles between them only fueled their love, as they navigated the complexities of distance with trust, open communication, and a firm belief in their love's strength. Their story is a testament to the power of love conquering all obstacles, proving that when two souls are destined to be together, no distance can keep them apart.

WWS_PhotoItem:101775573.caption: One of our  First Dates As a Couple!

WWS_PhotoItem:101775574.caption: Keke threw Dave a surprise birthday party

WWS_PhotoItem:101775576.caption: A few days before Keke goes back to Indonesia

WWS_PhotoItem:101775578.caption: Reuniting after almost a year apart in Seoul, South Korea

WWS_PhotoItem:101775579.caption: Our favorite bento restaurant in Pensacola, FL

WWS_PhotoItem:101775581.caption: Dave's first trip to Indonesia, where he discovered his one of favorite restaurant -Wing Heng. This place became a traditional spot to visit after arriving in Jakarta

WWS_PhotoItem:101775583.caption: Back to Jakarta for Prewedding photos :)

WWS_PhotoItem:101775584.caption: Last but not least, our favorite shot in series.

WWS_QuestionItem:101772816.question: Wow! Indonesia is far, will you hate us if we can't make it?
WWS_QuestionItem:101772816.answer: Absolutely not! We totally understand if you cannot make the long flight to Indonesia! We are still considering a US wedding/reception once our immigration procedure is completed. We will keep you all updated.

WWS_QuestionItem:101773172.question: How do we get to Indonesia?
WWS_QuestionItem:101773172.answer: Your best bet would be to fly to CGK (Jakarta airport code). You can take a boat or swim, but we do not recommend it and cannot be held accountable for any brave people who decide to take that route.

WWS_QuestionItem:101772939.question: This will be our first time in Indonesia, what can we expect?
WWS_QuestionItem:101772939.answer: Welcome! If you are planning to come, please do us a favor and RSVP ASAP. We totally understand if this is short notice for some people and cannot make it. After you confirm your attendance, Dave can reach out to help make arrangements (Flights/hotels/transport)

WWS_QuestionItem:101773098.question: Will there be any provided accommodations/transportation?
WWS_QuestionItem:101773098.answer:
At this time, there will not be any provided accommodations. However, there are definitely hotels that can fit your budget/preferences.

For transportation, please reach out to us directly to help organize transportation to/from the airport (CGK airport code)

window.UNION_INTERNAL_FRAGMENT_LOADER = ((expirationPeriod, cacheNamespace, window, document, storage, JSON, Date) => {
    const now = new Date;

    const createCacheStorage = () => {
      const getCacheKey = (fragment) => {
        return cacheNamespace + fragment.name;
      };

      const usedKeys = new Set();
      const unloadEvent = 'onpagehide' in window ? 'pagehide' : 'unload';
      window.addEventListener(unloadEvent, () => {
        Object.keys(storage).forEach((key) => {
          if (key.indexOf(cacheNamespace) === 0 && !usedKeys.has(key)) {
            storage.removeItem(key);
            console.warn('Deleting fragment cache: ', key);
          }
        });
      });

      return {
        set: (fragment, result) => {
          try {
            const key = getCacheKey(fragment);
            usedKeys.add(key);
            storage[key] = JSON.stringify([now, result]);
          } catch (error) {
            console.warn('Error hydrating fragment cache: ', error);
          }
        },
        get: (fragment) => {
          const key = getCacheKey(fragment)
          usedKeys.add(key);
          return storage[key];
        }
      }
    }

    const createHTMLFragmentLoader = () => {
      const cacheStorage = createCacheStorage();

      const performFetch = async (fragment) => {
        const response = await fetch(fragment.url)
        if (!response.ok) {
          console.warn('Unable to fetch fragment', fragment);
          return null;
        }

        return await response.text();
      }

      const performAppend = (fragment, targetElement, text) => {
        const domFragment = document.createRange()
          .createContextualFragment(
            '<!-- fragment start ' + fragment.id + '-->' + text + '<!-- fragment end -->'
          );
        domFragment.firstChild.id = fragment.id;
        targetElement.appendChild(domFragment);
      }

      const append = (fragment, text) => {
        let target = fragment.options.target;

        if (target !== 'head' && target !== 'body') {
          target = 'body';
        }

        const targetElement = document[target];

        if (target === 'body' && !targetElement) {
          document.addEventListener('readystatechange', function () {

            if (document.readyState === 'interactive')
              performAppend(fragment, document.body, text);
          });
          return;
        }

        performAppend(fragment, targetElement, text);
      }

      const fetchAppend = async (fragment) => {
        const text = await performFetch(fragment)
        if (text) {
          append(fragment, text);
        }
        return text;
      }

      const fetchAppendCache = async (fragment) => {
        const text = await fetchAppend(fragment)
        if (text)
          cacheStorage.set(fragment, text);
      }

      const fetchCache = async (fragment) => {
        const text = await performFetch(fragment)
        if (text)
          cacheStorage.set(fragment, text);
      }

      return {
        load: async (fragment) => {
          if (document.getElementById(fragment.id)) {
            console.log(fragment.id + ': Fragment is already in document. Avoiding load cycle.');
            return;
          }

          if (!fragment.options.cache) {
            return fetchAppend(fragment);
          }

          const cache = cacheStorage.get(fragment);

          if (!cache) {
            return fetchAppendCache(fragment);
          }

          const data = JSON.parse(cache);
          const lastUsed = new Date(data[0]);

          if (lastUsed > now /* Probably an attacker */) {
            return fetchAppendCache(fragment);
          }

          append(fragment, data[1]);

          setTimeout(() => {
            const timeSinceLastUsed = now - lastUsed;

            if (timeSinceLastUsed >= expirationPeriod) {
              fetchCache(fragment);
            }
          });
        }
      }
    }

    return createHTMLFragmentLoader();
  })(
    600000,
    'xou/fragments/',
    window,
    document,
    window.localStorage,
    JSON,
    Date
  );
</script>
